<recipe xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd">
  <title>Teresas Chilli</title>
  <filename>teresas_chilli.xml</filename>
  <htmlFilename>teresas_chilli.html</htmlFilename>
  <thumbnail>teresas_chilli.jpeg</thumbnail>
  <category>Beef</category>
  <category>Dinner</category>
  <ingredient>1 Kilo Minced Meat ( I use beef, Teresa uses Turkey)</ingredient>
  <ingredient>2 Celery Sticks chopped</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 Green pepper chopped</ingredient>
  <ingredient>3-4 garlic cloves crushed</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1/2 bunch parsley chopped</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 can or 2 fresh corn</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 carrot grated</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 can black beans</ingredient>
  <ingredient>2 cans chopped tomatoes</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1/2 cup tomatoe paste</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1-1/2 teaspoon chilli</ingredient>
  <ingredient>olive oil</ingredient>
  <ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
  <step>Heat oil in a large pot and then add garlic, cook for a few minutes before adding celery and pepper.</step>
  <step>Cook for two minutes more and add chilli powder then mince meat.</step>
  <step>Cook the meat until brown.</step>
  <step>Add all other ingredients and bring to the boil.</step>
  <step>Reduce to a simmer and cook for at least 1 hour.</step>
  <step>This gets better with age!  Serve with cheese on top and/or crusty bread if desired.</step>
</recipe>
